<tableCitation box="[1157,1241,943,969]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="4.[150,238,542,568]" captionTargetBox="[165,1966,655,1605]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="TABLE 1. Meristic values for Riffle Sculpin samples from the UC Davis Museum of Wildlife and Fish and the California Academy of Sciences, San Francisco. Cottus asper and C.pitensis data is presented for comparison.? means ‘could not be determined’. Locations include the year collected. See Table 2 for more precise location information. Sculpins at locations with * were C. asper originally identified as C. gulosus" pageId="16" pageNumber="517">Table 1</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
